-- Wapshott, Evans Discuss the Life and Legacy of Thatcher (Audio)
-- B y
-- 2013-04-09T14:12:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-09/wapshott-evans-discuss-the-life-and-legacy-of-thatcher-audio-.html
Nicholas Wapshott, a journalist and 
author of "Ronald Reagan and  Margaret Thatcher : A Political 
Marriage," and Sir Harold Evans, former editor of The Sunday 
Times and the London Times, discuss the passing of British Prime
Minister Margaret Thatcher. Wapshott and Evans talk with 
Bloomberg's Pimm Fox and Carol Massar on Bloomberg Radio's 
"Taking Stock."    (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 11:39
 